The paper discusses self-integrating systems in the context of Autonomic Computing, Internet of Things, and Industrial Internet. These topics are closely related to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. The paper also discusses error correction as an integrated element of bi-directional communication channels, which falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes to think of self-integration as sophisticated error correcting communications, which involves Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories.
